The article announces three nominations and appointments by the United States government. 

1. William W. Popp has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Guatemala. He is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Deputy Chief of Mission at the United States Embassy in Brasilia, Brazil. Popp has held various positions in different countries, including Kenya and Colombia. He has a B.A. from Westminster College, an M.A. from George Washington University, and an M.S. in National Security Strategy from the National War College. He speaks Spanish and Portuguese.

2. C. Kevin Blackstone has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste. Blackstone is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Executive Director of the Bureau of East Asian and Pacific Affairs at the Department of State. He has served in various management positions at U.S. Embassies in Egypt, Thailand, and India. Blackstone has a B.A. from the University of Virginia and an M.P.A. from the Maxwell School at Syracuse University. He speaks French and Italian.

3. Virginia Lamp Thomas has been appointed to be a Member of the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board.